Magnus Carlsen vs Peter Svidler
Steinitz Memorial (2020), 15.5.2020
Saragossa opening (A00)

Get the PGN here https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/fide-online-steinitz-memorial-2020/1/1/5

The FIDE Online Steinitz Memorial features two 10-player double round-robins taking place on chess24 from May 15-17 to celebrate the 1st World Chess Champion Wilhelm Steinitz (1836-1900). The total prize fund is €30,000, with Women's World Blitz Champion Kateryna Lagno top seed in the women's section.

The time control is 3 minutes per player for all moves, with a 2-second increment from move 1. No draw offers are allowed before move 30. A tie for 1st will be decided by an Armageddon game, where White has 5 minutes to Black's 4 but a draw counts as a win for Black.
